<HEADLINE>
FT  05 FEB 93 / World Commodities Prices: Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Base metals prices eased off their highs during late afternoon trading at
the London Metal Exchange. COPPER ran into technical resistance and Chinese
selling before ending after hours trading Dollars 6 up at Dollars 2,238 a
tonne in the three months position. The sterling quotation was Pounds 8.75
down at Pounds 1,560.50 a tonne as the pound clawed back some of its lost
ground. The three months ZINC price broke above the Dollars 1,130 level at
one stage, triggering some stop-loss buying orders, before settling back in
after hours trading to Dollars 1,129 a tonne, up Dollars 4.50 from
Wednesday. COCOA futures finished near the day's lows with sentiment on
charts becoming increasingly bearish. The May position ended Pounds 22 down
at the London Futures and Options Exchange. There continued to be
unconfirmed talk that Ivorian arrivals may have been higher than previously
believed. Robusta COFFEE futures managed to partially recoup earlier losses
during the afternoon session but the May position, which had dipped to
Dollars 910 at one stage, still finished Dollars 16 down at Dollars 928 a
tonne.
Compiled from Reuters
