<HEADLINE>
FT  05 FEB 93 / UK Company News: Bristol Channel incurs loss
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Recession coupled with difficult conditions in the shipping industry left
Bristol Channel Ship Repairers Pounds 236,261 in the red at the pre-tax
level for the 28 weeks to October 9.
The loss, which compared with previous profits of Pounds 74,884, was struck
after taking account of a special non-recurring item of Pounds 150,000.
Turnover fell from Pounds 661,801 to Pounds 34,192 and losses per share
amounted to 0.3p (earnings 0.09p).
Andreas Ugland, a private Norwegian shipping group, took a 24 per cent stake
in the company last July.
Developments at Bristol could result in Mr Christopher Bailey stepping down
as chairman.
