   By JOHN MASON, Law Courts Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR THOMAS Ward, the US lawyer who advised Guinness on its 1986 takeover of
Distillers, finished giving evidence at his trial yesterday.
Mr Ward, who denies stealing Pounds 5.2m from the company, rejected a
prosecution claim that he had concealed the payment from the Guinness board
because it had been dishonestly taken.
