</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE MAYOR of Rome and city council resigned yesterday, after a councillor
was arrested in a bribery inquiry, Reuter reports from Rome.
Mayor Franco Carraro, a Socialist and former minister in Italy's national
government, said the decision had been made with 'profound pain. It has
