<HEADLINE>
FT  04 FEB 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
After minor fluctuations around the 500 cents mark for the AWC market
indicator since sales were resumed in Australia, there was a more definite
decline on Tuesday. This took the indicator down by 10 cents and established
a new low for the 1992-93 season, 488c/kg. Withdrawals by growers were
heavier, approaching 20pc at the two centres. Sterling weakness has obvious
relevance to UK users of imported wool and prices have been advanced, but
business, whether home trade or export, is poor enough to make even these
increases difficult to establish.
