<TEXT>
TRENCOR, the Cape-based transport and trading company, is to gain control of
W&amp;A, a diversified South African consumer and industrial group, through a
capital injection of R350m (Dollars 113.6m).
The deal brings together two of South Africa's largest companies not
controlled by the country's big mining houses or financial institutions.
